# .gitignore — what Git should NOT save into this repository.
# This repo holds documentation (Markdown) and, later, a simple static
# website (HTML/CSS/JSON) written by the workers. There is no code to
# compile, no build process, and no API keys kept here. So this list is
# intentionally small: it mainly keeps out operating-system junk and
# anything that should never be made public, like secrets.

# Operating-system files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor / temporary files
*.swp
*~

# Secrets — never commit credentials, even though this system is
# designed not to use them. This is a safety backstop.
.env
*.key
*.pem

# Local logs
*.log